<HEADLINE>
<P>
MANILA SIGNS CEASE-FIRE WITH MUSLIM REBELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Philippine government signed a cease-fire pact Sunday with Muslim 
separatist guerrillas in another step toward ending a war that has killed more 
than 50,000 people in the last 20 years. 
</P>
<P>
 Manuel Yan, the chief Philippine negotiator in peace talks with the Moro 
National Liberation Front headed by Nur Misuari, signed the agreement after a 
government panel finished studying it. 
</P>
<P>
 Misuari signed the agreement Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
