<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUTTON AND JONES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Now that the shaking has stopped, more or less, I'd like to take a moment to 
offer a word of gratitude and praise for two women I think of as old friends, 
though I've never met them.I mean, of course, Kate Hutton of Caltech and Lucile 
Jones of the U.S. Geological Survey. I think of them familiarly as "Dr. Kate" 
and "Dr. Lucy," and through the years, after every earthquake, they have been a 
source of calm, rational information, at a time when rumors fly and alarmist 
predictions abound. 
</P>
<P>
 Thanks, Dr. Kate and Dr. Lucy -- I knew we could count on you! 
</P>
<P>
 LISABETH BROWNE, Costa Mesa 
</P>
</TEXT>
