<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: A HIGHLY EVOLVED AD CAMPAIGN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pepsi is counting on a couple of monkeys to help it overcome Coca-Cola's 
gaping lead in the global cola wars.Over the weekend, Pepsi Cola International 
fired its most ambitious salvo in the soft drink marketing battle outside the 
United States. 
</P>
<P>
 Its new commercial, aired in 28 markets to a potential audience of 500 million 
consumers, shows researchers experimenting on two chimps, giving a diet of 
Coca-Cola to one, Pepsi to the other. By the end of the test period, the chimp 
who drank Coca-Cola is making great strides, hammering pegs into the right 
holes, for example. 
</P>
<P>
 But the carefree Pepsi chimp is driving down a beach in a Jeep with several 
girls and a surfboard, music blaring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
