<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 FCC May OK Infinity Deal for KRTH-FM: Radio shock jock Howard Stern's employer 
may be allowed to buy the big Los Angeles station as FCC members back away from 
earlier threats to block the deal, the New York Times and the Washington Post 
reported last week. The FCC discussed penalizing Stern's employer by nixing the 
purchase, but the commission is concerned that such drastic punishment would be 
overturned in court, the newspapers said. A favorable decision for Infinity 
Broadcasting Corp. of New York is expected by Tuesday, the newspapers said. 
</P>
