<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; BETZOLD'S DOUBLE IN 11TH LIFTS THE TITANS OVER STANFORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jim Betzsold had a two-out, run-scoring double in the 11th inning to lift Cal 
State Fullerton to an 8-7 victory over Stanford in a nonconference baseball 
game Sunday at Stanford. 
</P>
<P>
 Betzsold's double scored Bret Hemphill, who had doubled with two outs. 
</P>
<P>
 Ted Silva (1-0), a sophomore right-hander, completed four innings of shutout 
relief for the victory. Cal State Fullerton (2-1) took two of three games in 
the season-opener for both teams. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton, ranked sixth by Baseball America, took a 6-0 lead with 
three runs each in the first and second innings. 
</P>
<P>
 The Titans built their lead because of a sloppy Cardinal defense. Stanford, 
ranked 12th in the same poll, made three errors that led to four unearned runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Dante Powell had two hits, scored two runs, drove in one and stole four bases. 
Craig Skyberg had a hit and also scored two runs for Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Dan Ricabal, 11-3 last season as a starter for the Titans, failed to hold the 
early 6-0 lead. He allowed four runs in the third to cut the Titan lead to 6-4. 
Cal State Fullerton scored in the fourth to take a 7-4 lead but Ricabal allowed 
three more runs in the fifth. He gave up six earned runs, walked three and 
struck out four. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Wagner replaced Ricabal to start the sixth and had three strikeouts in 
two shutout innings before Silva came in. 
</P>
<P>
 Tom Reimers (0-1) allowed seven hits and one run in 7 2/3 innings of relief 
but took the loss as Stanford fell to 1-2. 
</P>
<P>
 The Titans play UC Riverside at 2:30 p.m. Tuesday in their home opener. Cal 
State Fullerton then plays host to Arizona for a three-game series starting at 
7 p.m. Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 In a Mountain Pacific Sports Federation men's volleyball match: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific 3, UC Irvine 0 -- Darren Lance and Sam Crosson each had 15 kills for 
host Pacific, which won, 15-7, 15-12, 15-8. Leland Quinn had 16 kills and Evan 
Alexander added 11 for UC Irvine (1-3, 1-1). 
</P>
