<HEADLINE>
<P>
TO OUR SUBSCRIBERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Effective today, the home-delivered price of The Times will change 2% to $3.92 
per week for daily and Sunday service.The new rate for daily-only home delivery 
will be $3.38 per week. These rates include applicable California sales taxes. 
</P>
<P>
 There will be no change for Sunday-only service and no change in single copy 
rates. 
</P>
<P>
 This small increase in home delivery subscription rates reflects higher 
distribution and operating costs as well as ongoing editorial improvements at 
The Times. 
</P>
<P>
 The new rates will go into effect in those parts of Los Angeles, Ventura, San 
Bernardino, Riverside and Santa Barbara counties in which subscribers are 
billed directly by The Times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
