<P>
 About 600 football fans from Mexico were cheated out of about $500,000 in a 
phony Super Bowl ticket scam.About 80 police from College Park, Ga., were 
called to a hotel ballroom Saturday night, where angry fans had created a 
disturbance after learning that they had no Super Bowl tickets. The fans had 
bought a travel package that was to include air travel, lodging and tickets. 
The fans didn't buy the theory that two out of three ain't bad. After police 
escorted the Atlanta travel representative, who police say was also a victim of 
the scam, out of the building, the crowd quieted. 
