<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; TEEN DIES IN GANG DISPUTE, POLICE SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A teen-ager was fatally shot as he tried to run away following a dispute over 
gang membership, Santa Ana police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The 15-year-old, whom police would not identify because of his age, was shot 
in the 1300 block of South Center Street, said Cpl.Bill Barrett, who said 
police are searching for three suspects in the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-ager, who was from Santa Ana, and two friends went to a party on 
Center Street shortly after midnight where they were confronted by several gang 
members, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The trio tried to leave the party but were followed by the gang members, who 
drove after the group, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A passenger in the car jumped out and began fighting with the victim, who was 
shot as he tried to run away, Barrett said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
