<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA NIGUEL; GRANTS AVAILABLE FOR SERVICE, ART GROUPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICHARD CORE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Community service and arts organizations in the city can apply for grants 
being made available by the City Council. Deadline for applications is Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council has allocated $14,225 for grants to community services 
organizations and $10,625 for arts groups in 1994. Last year, grants ranging 
from $1,000 to $5,000 were awarded to such recipients as homeless and 
children's shelters, performance troupes and singing groups, said Pamela 
Lawrence, assistant to the city manager. 
</P>
<P>
 All requests for funds will be considered and reviewed by a council-appointed 
committee, which makes recommendations to the council. Highest priority will be 
given to organizations and programs that provide direct service or benefit to 
the greatest number of city residents, Lawrence said. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications must be received by 5 p.m. Friday at City Hall, 27801 La Paz 
Road, to be considered for funding. Grant awards will be made by the City 
Council no later than March 15. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information or to request an application, call (714) 362-4300. 
RICHARD CORE 
</P>
