<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 ARRESTED IN HUNTINGTON ROBBERY, BEATING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three transients were arrested on suspicion of armed robbery late Saturday 
after they beat and robbed a Costa Mesa man who was walking in the flood 
control channel, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Pablo Gavino Rosas, 32, was attacked about 7:30 p.m. as he walked under a 
bridge at Hamilton Avenue near Brookhurst Street.The men hit Rosas, knocked him 
down and kicked him before stealing his radio, a small amount of cash and some 
beer, Lt. Jeff Cope said. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects -- identified as Oerliso Ortunio, 28, Jaime Laredo Aquino, 39, 
and Manuel Rio Salcedo, 29 -- were arrested after police found them hiding 
under a nearby bridge a short time later, police said. Each was being held in 
the Huntington Beach Jail Sunday on $50,000 bail. 
</P>
