</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ANGELES TIMES SPECIAL REPORT; IMAGES OF THE NORTHRIDGE EARTHQUAKE; SHAKEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Night. Silence. Then the shaking began, 11 miles deep in the ground.In an 
instant, the tremors burst from the earth like a malevolent spirit escaping 
from some infernal region of myth and nightmare. 
</P>
<P>
 Later, the experts would say the quake lasted only 10 seconds, but in the 
quivering hearts of survivors, it seemed far longer. Instead of fading after 
the first violent spasms, the shaking intensified its destructive work, 
snapping thick, steel beams on freeways like bread sticks, crushing apartment 
buildings and, above all, rewriting the future of Los Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
