<LENGTH>
<P>
81 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ANGELES TIMES SPECIAL REPORT; IMAGES OF THE NORTHRIDGE EARTHQUAKE; HELP; 
PROVIDING REFUGE AND AID THROUGH DIFFICULT DAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aid flooded in, millions and millions of dollars of it. 
</P>
<P>
 Suddenly, the scenes of tent cities and food lines we had watched on 
television, beamed into our living rooms from some faraway place, were 
happening next door. 
</P>
<P>
 The Red Cross and the Salvation Army set up shelters and the National Guard 
patrolled the streets for looters. But it seemed that crooks were shaken out of 
their routine along with everyone else. Even with rubble in them, the streets 
were safer than usual. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA013194-0204 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 008953 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
